Analysis of the Target Structure

• Block Count & Layers  
  – Total of 4 blocks used.  
  – They form two “levels.”  
     1) Bottom Level: one vertical orange cylinder in the center, flanked on each side by an orange triangular wedge.  
     2) Top Level: a single red half‐cylinder cradle block perched horizontally atop the cylinder.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The orange cylinder stands upright at the center of the base.  
  – One orange triangular wedge is snug against the left side of the cylinder (right‐angled face toward the cylinder).  
  – Another orange triangular wedge is snug against the right side of the cylinder (again, right‐angled face toward the cylinder).  
  – The red “U”‐shaped cradle block caps the cylinder from above, with its curved underside fitting onto the top of the cylinder.  

Selecting Blocks from the Dictionary

• Needed Blocks & Indices  
  1) Red cradle block (index 1) – matches the top piece with a half‐cylinder cutout underneath.  
  2) Orange vertical cylinder (index 7) – matches the tall orange cylinder.  
  3) Orange left‐side triangular wedge (index 14).  
  4) Orange right‐side triangular wedge (index 13).  

Step‐By‐Step Assembly

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 7  
  Step2: Move block with index 14  
  Step3: Move block with index 13  
  Step4: Move block with index 1  
}
